workflow.name: Automate corporate tax filing for SMEs with GPT-5.2-Pro, Gmail, and Google Drive
workflow.description:
## How It Works
This workflow automates monthly tax filing processes by retrieving financial data, performing AI-driven tax calculations, coordinating pre-filing reviews with key stakeholders, incorporating feedback, and managing overall submission readiness. It pulls accounting records, executes GPT-5‚Äìbased tax calculations with transparent reasoning, formats comprehensive pre-filing reports, and routes them to a submission coordinator via email for review. The system captures reviewer feedback through structured prompts, intelligently applies necessary corrections, archives finalized records in Google Drive, and continuously tracks filing status. It is designed for accounting firms, tax practices, and finance departments that require coordinated, multi-stakeholder tax filing with minimal manual intervention.

## Setup Steps
1. Connect accounting system and configure financial data fetch parameters.
2. Set up OpenAI GPT-4 API for tax calculations and reasoning extraction.
3. Configure Gmail, Chat Model, and Google Drive credentials.
4. Define submission coordinator contacts and configure feedback.

## Prerequisites
Accounting system access; OpenAI API key; Gmail account; Google Drive
## Use Cases
Tax firms managing multi-client monthly filings with partner review  
## Customization
Modify tax calculation prompts for jurisdictions, adjust feedback collection fields 
## Benefits
Eliminates manual filing coordination, reduces submission errors

workflow.name: GPT-5.2-Pro SME Corporate Tax Filing and Compliance Automation

options.systemMessage:
You are a corporate tax calculation assistant for SMEs.

Your task is to:
1. Analyze the monthly financial data provided (revenue, expenses, cost of goods sold)
2. Calculate the gross profit (revenue - cost of goods sold)
3. Calculate the net profit (gross profit - operating expenses)
4. Determine taxable income by applying standard deductions
5. Calculate the tax liability using the applicable tax rate
6. Use the Calculator tool for all arithmetic operations
7. Return the results in the structured format defined by the output parser

Be precise with calculations and show your work step by step.

assignments.name: reportSummary
assignments.value:
={{ 'Gross Profit: $' + $json.grossProfit + '
Net Profit: $' + $json.netProfit + '
Taxable Income: $' + $json.taxableIncome + '
Tax Liability: $' + $json.taxLiability + '
Effective Tax Rate: ' + ($json.effectiveTaxRate * 100) + '%' }}

options.systemMessage:
You are a tax filing submission coordinator for SMEs.

Your task is to:
1. Send the pre-filing tax report to the tax agent via email using the Gmail Send Tool
   - Recipient: Use the taxAgentEmail from the workflow data
   - Subject: "Monthly Tax Pre-Filing Report - [Company Name] - [Month Year]"
   - Body: Include the report summary and all calculation details in a professional format
2. Archive the report in the compliance vault using the Google Drive Archive Tool
   - File name: "Tax_Report_[Company]_[YYYY-MM].json"
   - Folder ID: Use the complianceVaultFolderId from the workflow data
   - Content: Full JSON report with all tax calculations
3. Confirm both actions were completed successfully

Use the tools to execute these tasks and report the results.

data.details:
The IF node can be used to implement binary conditional logic in your workflow. You can set up one-to-many conditions to evaluate each item of data being inputted into the node. That data will either evaluate to TRUE or FALSE and route out of the node accordingly.

This node has multiple types of conditions: Bool, String, Number, and Date & Time.
